489
00:28:54,538 --> 00:28:55,339
Let's welcome him.

490
00:28:57,419 --> 00:28:59,179
(The worst-case scenario just happened.)

491
00:28:59,899 --> 00:29:02,859
(I know I'm standing
on the edge of a cliff right now.)

492
00:29:09,058 --> 00:29:10,738
- Hello, Mr. Gao.
- Hello, Miss Sun.

493
00:29:11,698 --> 00:29:14,258
Miss Xu, what a coincidence
to see you here.

494
00:29:16,179 --> 00:29:17,738
Mr. Gao, do you know Xu Yan?

495
00:29:18,339 --> 00:29:19,419
We know each other well.

496
00:29:20,698 --> 00:29:21,978
Where did you two meet?

497
00:29:22,899 --> 00:29:24,538
I... I don't really remember.

498
00:29:25,738 --> 00:29:26,939
I don't know where.

499
00:29:28,218 --> 00:29:28,778
You...

500
00:29:29,579 --> 00:29:30,339
Look at her.

501
00:29:30,738 --> 00:29:31,339
It's okay.

502
00:29:31,538 --> 00:29:32,538
Let's sit down and talk.

503
00:29:32,698 --> 00:29:33,419
Alright.

504
00:29:42,339 --> 00:29:42,939
Mr. Gao,

505
00:29:43,258 --> 00:29:44,859
may I ask what the reason was

506
00:29:44,859 --> 00:29:47,339
that made you impersonate
a wedding guest?

507
00:29:49,778 --> 00:29:52,619
Actually, many people
sought me out before.

508
00:29:52,859 --> 00:29:56,218
Some did so
because their families lack members.

509
00:29:56,659 --> 00:29:58,379
They wanted me to liven things up.

510
00:29:58,698 --> 00:30:00,899
Others did it purely for appearances.

511
00:30:01,258 --> 00:30:04,379
They were afraid
the event wouldn't measure up

512
00:30:04,419 --> 00:30:05,339
to the in-laws.

513
00:30:06,298 --> 00:30:08,258
Were there any cases
of marriage fraud among them?

514
00:30:13,778 --> 00:30:15,298
Yes, there were.

515
00:30:18,419 --> 00:30:22,419
Mr. Gao, this could be seen as fraud.

516
00:30:22,538 --> 00:30:25,018
Once exposed,
you might face criminal charges.

517
00:30:26,458 --> 00:30:28,099
It was always the bride
committing fraud.

518
00:30:28,698 --> 00:30:30,899
I only found out afterwards.

519
00:30:31,139 --> 00:30:33,258
I really regretted it.

520
00:30:33,298 --> 00:30:34,619
I really did.

521
00:30:34,659 --> 00:30:36,859
I shouldn't have gone along with them.

522
00:30:37,619 --> 00:30:40,579
We can see that Mr. Gao
has reflected deeply.

523
00:30:40,659 --> 00:30:42,538
It's alright.
We learn from our mistakes.

524
00:30:43,298 --> 00:30:45,139
As law-abiding citizens,

525
00:30:45,179 --> 00:30:47,018
- we must follow the law.
- Yes.

526
00:30:47,058 --> 00:30:49,450
- We must not go down the wrong path.
- Yes.

527
00:30:54,288 --> 00:30:56,976
Mr. Gao, the person
in the photo is you, right?

528
00:30:57,468 --> 00:30:58,738
Yes, that's me.

529
00:30:59,978 --> 00:31:02,619
What role did you play at the wedding?

530
00:31:03,579 --> 00:31:04,339
The bride's father.

531
00:31:05,018 --> 00:31:06,458
It's a double fate.

532
00:31:06,538 --> 00:31:07,419
Double fate.

533
00:31:20,458 --> 00:31:21,659
Isn't this Ms. Xu's wedding?

534
00:31:21,978 --> 00:31:23,179
What's going on?

535
00:31:23,339 --> 00:31:24,819
Was he at her wedding ceremony?

536
00:31:25,099 --> 00:31:27,058
I must say, they do look alike.

537
00:31:33,619 --> 00:31:34,298
Mr. Gao,

538
00:31:36,058 --> 00:31:37,018
what about this photo?

539
00:31:46,939 --> 00:31:47,458
Well...

540
00:31:47,619 --> 00:31:48,458
What do you mean?

541
00:31:51,018 --> 00:31:55,819
I discovered by chance
while investigating this news story

542
00:31:55,899 --> 00:32:00,258
that Mr. Gao and Xu Yan's father
might be the same person.

543
00:32:00,778 --> 00:32:03,538
As journalists,
we need to get to the bottom of things

544
00:32:03,579 --> 00:32:04,939
and pursue the truth.

